OL,3,C'Miscarriage of justice' fears over
OL,4,Cbrother and sister's deaths in
OL,5,CPembrokeshire
OL,7,FGriff and Patti Thomas, aged 73 and
OL,8,F70, were living at Ffynnon Samson farm
OL,9,Fin Llangolman. Both were unmarried and
OL,10,Fhad lived together throughout their
OL,11,Flives.
OL,13,FHowever, on December 11, 1976, a
OL,14,Fmurder investigation was launched
OL,15,Fafter their bodies were discovered in
OL,16,Ftheir home. Two months later, the
OL,17,Finquiry concluded that Patti had been
OL,18,Funlawfully killed after suffering an
OL,19,Fassault at the hands of her brother.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/11
